# CAD — SlimPad Case

3D printed two-part case for the SlimPad macropad.

## Files
- `slimpad_top.stl` — top plate with switch cutouts, OLED window and encoder hole
- `slimpad_bottom.stl` — bottom case with USB-C cutout and standoffs

## What it looks like
![Case exploded view](cad.jpg)
![Case assembled](cad1.jpg)

## Dimensions
| Part | Value |
|------|-------|
| Outer size | 104 × 104 mm |
| Total height | ~13 mm assembled |
| Switch holes | 14 × 14 mm (MX standard) |
| Switch grid | 3×4, 19mm pitch |
| OLED window | 26 × 10 mm |
| Encoder hole | 7 mm diameter |
| USB-C cutout | 9 × 3.5 mm |

## Print Settings
| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Material | PLA or PETG |
| Layer height | 0.2 mm |
| Infill | 20% |
| Walls | 3 |
| Supports | No |
| Gap between parts | 0.2 mm tolerance |

## Assembly
1. Press 4× M3×5mm×4mm heatset inserts into bottom case corners
2. Place PCB onto standoffs
3. Snap top plate over switches
4. Secure with 4× M3×16mm screws from bottom
